## What Minimum Viable OMF Costs

For a mid-sized Web3 ecosystem (treasury $5–20M), the first-year cost of a minimum viable OMF implementation:

| Component | Estimated Cost |
|---|---|
| Dependency audit (60-day contractor engagement) | $15–30K |
| Governance proposal facilitation | $5–10K |
| Retainer program (3–5 projects, 6-month initial) + 1 Pathway cohort | $200–400K/yr |
| Mid-point review and reporting | $10K |
| Renewal cycle + initial Resilience programs | $50–100K |
| **Total Year 1** | **$280–570K** |

This is well within 5–10% of a $5M treasury's operational budget — and far less than the cost of a single major security incident in critical infrastructure.

---

*Portability is OMF's central claim. For that claim to be meaningful, the minimum implementation must be precisely defined. These five requirements are the definition.*
